<br>
What I do wonder is after our recent past conflicts, and after 9/11 people refuse to believe that our cournty can not field accurate data.  I remember after the first 48 hours of 9/11 you where hearing unconfirmed reports of Bin Ladin and Al Qeida (sp) being behind the attack.  I would guess that is some pretty fast and accurate info gathering.  <br>
<br>
Why if you trusted their actions against Afganastan (which were primarily unfounded since it was just the Bush administration telling us they knew afganistan/taliban/Bin Ladin had a hand in it) would you have reason to doubt the same administration from knowing the data they have now?<br>
<br>
I think Bush is laying a heavy american hand on the situation, but if you remember his actions from 9/11 he was very slow to act.  People of the nation were outraged, many people were crying for blood.  The american people in our pain and need to defend ourselves from that terrible act would have not cared who we attacked/destroyed till after the dust settled, but our leaders made the right choices..they had temperence in a time of pain and when we as a country felt the need to lash out they didn't knee jerk....<br>
<br>
Granted we are all humans even the people we elect as our leaders but why second guess people who has proven that they get what they think is the correct information and act upon it with apporpriate messure with minimal civilan casualties, and American lives.<br>
<br>
They may not be making the correct choice in their action, but I'm pretty sure they know what they claim to be true is probably true. <p><center><table border="2" bordercolor="black"> 
